{
  "video_id": "8HegwRtbDSU",
  "title": "The fascinating history of cemeteries - Keith Eggener",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 6965.0,
      "end_time": 9205.0,
      "text": "Spindly trees,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 9205.0,
      "end_time": 11150.0,
      "text": "rusted gates,"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 11150.0,
      "end_time": 13195.0,
      "text": "crumbling stone,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 13195.0,
      "end_time": 15425.0,
      "text": "a solitary mourner—"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 15425.0,
      "end_time": 18955.0,
      "text": "these things come to mind  when we think of cemeteries."
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 18955.0,
      "end_time": 20354.0,
      "text": "But not so long ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 20355.0,
      "end_time": 22945.0,
      "text": "many burial grounds were lively places,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 22945.0,
      "end_time": 29055.0,
      "text": "with blooming gardens and crowds of people strolling among the headstones."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 29105.0,
      "end_time": 32255.0,
      "text": "How did our cemeteries  become what they are today?"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 32255.000000000004,
      "end_time": 34485.0,
      "text": "Some have been around for centuries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 34485.0,
      "end_time": 37495.0,
      "text": "like the world’s largest, Wadi al-Salaam,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 37495.0,
      "end_time": 40535.0,
      "text": "where more than five million  people are buried."
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 40535.0,
      "end_time": 44598.0,
      "text": "But most of the places we’d recognize  as cemeteries are much younger."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 44598.0,
      "end_time": 46458.0,
      "text": "In fact, for much of human history,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 46458.0,
      "end_time": 48798.0,
      "text": "we didn’t bury our dead at all."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 48798.0,
      "end_time": 53468.0,
      "text": "Our ancient ancestors had many other ways  of parting with the dead loved ones."
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 53468.0,
      "end_time": 55451.0,
      "text": "Some were left in caves,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 55451.0,
      "end_time": 56791.0,
      "text": "others in trees"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 56791.0,
      "end_time": 58601.0,
      "text": "or on mountaintops."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 58601.0,
      "end_time": 60811.0,
      "text": "Still others were sunk in lakes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 60811.0,
      "end_time": 62181.0,
      "text": "put out to sea,"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 62181.0,
      "end_time": 64410.0,
      "text": "ritually cannibalized,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 64410.0,
      "end_time": 65831.0,
      "text": "or cremated."
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 65831.0,
      "end_time": 67581.0,
      "text": "All of these practices,"
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 67581.0,
      "end_time": 69691.0,
      "text": "though some may seem strange today,"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 69691.0,
      "end_time": 72228.0,
      "text": "were ways of venerating the dead."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 72228.0,
      "end_time": 74857.0,
      "text": "By contrast, the first known burials"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 74858.0,
      "end_time": 77318.0,
      "text": "about 120,000 years ago"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 77318.0,
      "end_time": 79848.0,
      "text": "were likely reserved for transgressors,"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 79848.0,
      "end_time": 84708.0,
      "text": "excluding them from the usual rites intended to honor the dead."
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 84708.0,
      "end_time": 88758.0,
      "text": "But the first burials revealed some advantages over other practices:"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 88758.0,
      "end_time": 92980.0,
      "text": "they protected bodies from scavengers  and the elements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 92980.0,
      "end_time": 95818.0,
      "text": "while shielding loved ones from the  sight of decay."
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 95818.0,
      "end_time": 101398.0,
      "text": "These benefits may have shifted  ancient people’s thinking toward graves designed to honor the dead,"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 101468.0,
      "end_time": 103808.0,
      "text": "and burial became more common."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 103808.0,
      "end_time": 107178.0,
      "text": "Sometimes, these graves contained  practical or ritual objects,"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 107178.0,
      "end_time": 109128.0,
      "text": "suggesting belief in an afterlife, when the dead might need such tools."
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 112338.0,
      "end_time": 116710.0,
      "text": "Communal burials first appeared in North  Africa and West Asia"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 116710.0,
      "end_time": 119660.0,
      "text": "around 10 to 15,000 years ago,"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 119660.0,
      "end_time": 124690.0,
      "text": "around the same time as the first  permanent settlements in these areas."
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 124690.0,
      "end_time": 129130.0,
      "text": "These burial grounds created permanent  places to commemorate the dead."
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 129130.0,
      "end_time": 135260.0,
      "text": "The nomadic Scythians littered the steppes with grave mounds known as kurgans."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 135300.0,
      "end_time": 138640.0,
      "text": "The Etruscans built expansive necropoles,"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 138640.0,
      "end_time": 141980.0,
      "text": "their grid-patterned streets  lined with tombs."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 141980.0,
      "end_time": 145149.0,
      "text": "In Rome, subterranean catacombs housed"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 145150.0,
      "end_time": 148850.0,
      "text": "both cremation urns and intact remains."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 148850.0,
      "end_time": 152620.0,
      "text": "The word cemetery, or “sleeping chamber,”"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 152620.0,
      "end_time": 155400.0,
      "text": "was first used by ancient Greeks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 155400.0,
      "end_time": 159459.0,
      "text": "who built tombs in graveyards at the edges of their cities."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 159470.0,
      "end_time": 161160.0,
      "text": "In medieval European cities,"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 161160.0,
      "end_time": 164256.0,
      "text": "Christian churchyards provided  rare, open spaces"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 164256.0,
      "end_time": 165646.0,
      "text": "that accommodated the dead,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 165646.0,
      "end_time": 169106.0,
      "text": "but also hosted markets, fairs,  and other events."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 169106.0,
      "end_time": 171460.0,
      "text": "Farmers even grazed cattle in them,"
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 171460.0,
      "end_time": 175600.0,
      "text": "believing graveyard grass made  for sweeter milk."
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 175600.0,
      "end_time": 178660.0,
      "text": "As cities grew during the industrial  revolution,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 178660.0,
      "end_time": 183426.0,
      "text": "large suburban cemeteries replaced  smaller urban churchyards."
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 183426.0,
      "end_time": 187766.0,
      "text": "Cemeteries like the 110-acre  Père-Lachaise in Paris"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 187766.0,
      "end_time": 192706.0,
      "text": "or the 72-acre Mt. Auburn  in Cambridge, Massachusetts"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 192706.0,
      "end_time": 194636.0,
      "text": "were lushly landscaped gardens"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 194636.0,
      "end_time": 196636.0,
      "text": "filled with sculpted stones"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 196636.0,
      "end_time": 198946.0,
      "text": "and ornate tombs."
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 198946.0,
      "end_time": 202186.0,
      "text": "Once a luxury reserved for the rich  and powerful,"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 202186.0,
      "end_time": 207656.0,
      "text": "individually marked graves became available to the middle  and working classes."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 207726.0,
      "end_time": 210160.0,
      "text": "People visited cemeteries for funerals,"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 210160.0,
      "end_time": 212685.0,
      "text": "but also for anniversaries, holidays,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 212686.0,
      "end_time": 216660.0,
      "text": "or simply an afternoon outdoors."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 216660.0,
      "end_time": 221770.0,
      "text": "By the late 19th century, as more public  parks and botanical gardens appeared,"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 221770.0,
      "end_time": 223497.0,
      "text": "cemeteries began to lose visitors."
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 223497.0,
      "end_time": 227346.0,
      "text": "Today, many old cemeteries are  lonely places."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 227346.0,
      "end_time": 230860.0,
      "text": "Some are luring visitors back with tours,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 230860.0,
      "end_time": 232336.0,
      "text": "concerts, and other attractions."
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 232336.0,
      "end_time": 234616.0,
      "text": "But even as we revive old cemeteries,"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 234616.0,
      "end_time": 237396.0,
      "text": "we’re rethinking the future of burial."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 237396.0,
      "end_time": 240386.0,
      "text": "Cities like London, New York, and  Hong Kong"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 240386.0,
      "end_time": 242636.0,
      "text": "are running out of burial space."
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 242636.0,
      "end_time": 245286.0,
      "text": "Even in places where space isn’t so tight,"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 245286.0,
      "end_time": 247656.0,
      "text": "cemeteries permanently occupy land"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 247656.0,
      "end_time": 250776.0,
      "text": "that can’t be otherwise cultivated  or developed."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 250776.0,
      "end_time": 253426.0,
      "text": "Traditional burial consumes materials"
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 253426.0,
      "end_time": 256464.0,
      "text": "like metal, stone, and concrete,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 256464.0,
      "end_time": 261450.0,
      "text": "and can pollute soil and groundwater with toxic chemicals."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 261450.0,
      "end_time": 263755.0,
      "text": "With increasing awareness of the  environmental costs,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 263755.0,
      "end_time": 266165.0,
      "text": "people are seeking alternatives."
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 266165.0,
      "end_time": 269745.0,
      "text": "Many are turning to cremation and  related practices."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 269745.0,
      "end_time": 271985.0,
      "text": "Along with these more conventional  practices,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 271985.0,
      "end_time": 274835.0,
      "text": "people can now have their remains  shot into space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 274835.0,
      "end_time": 276995.0,
      "text": "used to fertilize a tree,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 276995.0,
      "end_time": 278405.0,
      "text": "or made into jewelry,"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 278405.0,
      "end_time": 279594.0,
      "text": "fireworks,"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 279595.0,
      "end_time": 282950.0,
      "text": "and even tattoo ink."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 282102.0,
      "end_time": 286602.0,
      "text": "In the future, options like these may  replace burial completely."
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 286602.0,
      "end_time": 290572.0,
      "text": "Cemeteries may be our most familiar  monuments to the departed,"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 290572.0,
      "end_time": 297382.0,
      "text": "but they’re just one step in our ever-evolving process of remembering and honoring the dead."
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 297400.0,
      "end_time": 303000.0,
      "text": "All living things die, but is resurrection possible?"
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 303000.0,
      "end_time": 307400.0,
      "text": "And, what's the actual difference between a living creature and a dead body anyway?"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 307400.0,
      "end_time": 310000.0,
      "text": "Check out this lesson to find out."
    }
  ]
}